@page "/crafting"

<div class="card-container">
    <Pages.Components.CardComponent Header="Crafting in Reign of Humanae">
        <p>
            In <strong>Reign of Humanae</strong>, the crafting system is an essential part of the gameplay, allowing
            players to create unique items based on their race's special abilities. Here's how crafting works, along
            with some tips to master the system:
        </p>

        <div class="card-divider"></div>

        <Pages.Components.CardComponent Header="Race-Specific Crafting">
            <p>
                Each race has the ability to craft distinct items that reflect their cultural and technological
                strengths. For example, Dwarfs excel in creating powerful technological items, while Elves are skilled
                in crafting items infused with nature magic.
            </p>
            <ul>
                <li><strong>Understand Your Race's Strengths:</strong> Focus on crafting items that align with your
                    race's unique abilities to maximize efficiency and effectiveness.</li>
                <li><strong>Collaborate with Other Races:</strong> Trade and collaborate with players from other races
                    to obtain unique items and crafting recipes that your race cannot create alone.</li>
            </ul>
        </Pages.Components.CardComponent>

        <div class="card-divider"></div>

        <Pages.Components.CardComponent Header="Master Blacksmiths">
            <p>
                Players can become master blacksmiths within their race. A master blacksmith has the ability to sell
                crafting instructions (recipes) to players from other races, allowing for cross-cultural item creation.
            </p>
            <ul>
                <li><strong>Aspire to Become a Master:</strong> Focus on improving your crafting skills and unlocking
                    advanced recipes to become a sought-after master blacksmith.</li>
                <li><strong>Build a Reputation:</strong> As a master blacksmith, cultivate a network of clients and
                    allies to expand your influence and business opportunities across races.</li>
            </ul>
        </Pages.Components.CardComponent>

        <div class="card-divider"></div>

        <Pages.Components.CardComponent Header="Material Requirements">
            <p>
                Crafting items requires specific materials that players must gather or acquire. These materials can be
                found through exploration, quests, or trade with other players.
            </p>
            <ul>
                <li><strong>Gather Resources Efficiently:</strong> Plan your exploration to gather rare and essential
                    materials for crafting projects. Know the best locations and times to find them.</li>
                <li><strong>Participate in Quests:</strong> Complete quests to earn special materials and recipes that
                    are otherwise unavailable, increasing your crafting potential.</li>
                <li><strong>Engage in Trade:</strong> Trade excess materials with other players to acquire what you
                    need, creating mutually beneficial exchanges.</li>
            </ul>
        </Pages.Components.CardComponent>

        <div class="card-divider"></div>

        <Pages.Components.CardComponent Header="Crafting Mechanics">
            <p>
                Players use crafting stations or forges to create items. The crafting process may involve mini-games or
                challenges that can affect the quality and power of the crafted item.
            </p>
            <ul>
                <li><strong>Master the Mini-Games:</strong> Practice the mini-games or challenges associated with
                    crafting to improve the quality of your items.</li>
                <li><strong>Optimize Crafting Time:</strong> Use crafting stations efficiently, prioritizing high-demand
                    items and managing your time to maximize output.</li>
            </ul>
        </Pages.Components.CardComponent>

        <div class="card-divider"></div>

        <Pages.Components.CardComponent Header="Skill Improvement">
            <p>
                Players improve their crafting skills by actively engaging in crafting activities. As players become
                more skilled, they gain access to more advanced recipes and can create higher-quality items.
            </p>
            <ul>
                <li><strong>Practice Regularly:</strong> Engage in crafting consistently to gradually improve your
                    skills and unlock new recipes.</li>
                <li><strong>Set Goals:</strong> Establish specific goals for skill improvement and track your progress
                    to stay motivated and focused.</li>
            </ul>
        </Pages.Components.CardComponent>

        <div class="card-divider"></div>

        <Pages.Components.CardComponent Header="Customization and Upgrades">
            <p>
                Crafted items can be customized or upgraded with additional materials or enchantments to enhance their
                attributes. This allows players to tailor their equipment to their playstyle and needs.
            </p>
            <ul>
                <li><strong>Experiment with Enchantments:</strong> Test different combinations of materials and
                    enchantments to discover powerful synergies that enhance your items.</li>
                <li><strong>Focus on Versatility:</strong> Craft items that can be easily upgraded or adapted to
                    different scenarios, ensuring they remain useful as your character progresses.</li>
            </ul>
        </Pages.Components.CardComponent>
    </Pages.Components.CardComponent>
</div>
